node.title: The blurred lines surrounding music copyrights
node.description: Song composition has become an increasingly disharmonious area of litigation, as more and more songwriters are being taken to court when two songs share a melody, some chords, or even just a vibe.

node.title: What is Putin's endgame now?

node.title: 6 dead and at least 9 injured in shooting in Sacramento, police say

node.title: Ukraine documents alleged atrocities by retreating Russians

node.title: Ann-Margret

node.title: Ukraine sees openings as Russians focus on besieged Mariupol

node.title: Insurance Council calls for NZ to invest in climate change mitigation measures

node.title: Moana Jackson tangi: Thousands pay their respects

node.title: Covid-19: More than half of Healthline calls abandoned during Delta outbreak
